text: Kemiönsaari is a municipality in Southwest Finland. As of January 2014 about 7,000 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Salo, Raasepori, Hanko, Parainen and Sauvo. It was created on 1 January 2009, when the former municipalities of Dragsfjärd, Kimito and Västanfjärd were merged into the municipality. Most people in Kemiönsaari speak Swedish. == Other websites == * * website, English (Finish and Swedish pages also available) Category:Municipalities of Southwest Finland
